ashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class="reviewer">\n				Par <a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/duffdaddy"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4e1ef4834d9bc9d62bc5036aaeb8335b?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4e1ef4834d9bc9d62bc5036aaeb8335b?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/duffdaddy" class="reviewer-name">Duffdaddy</a> le <span class="review-date">août 25, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class="review-body">Have used this plugin a lot for client sites.\nIt\'s easy to implement and clients understand how it works which is a huge plus.\nGenerally very few problems or incompatibilities.\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="review">\n	<div class="review-head">\n		<div class="reviewer-info">\n			<div class="review-title-section">\n				<h4 class="review-title">Deleted all categories on uninstall</h4>\n				<div class="star-rating">\n				<div class="wporg-ratings" aria-label="1 sur 5 étoiles" data-title-template="%s sur 5 étoiles" data-rating="1" style="color:#ffb900;"><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class="reviewer">\n				Par <a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/eccebombo"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a4ad41d5d5004ec8904e6c56df33e285?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a4ad41d5d5004ec8904e6c56df33e285?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/eccebombo" class="reviewer-name">adrianogiannacco <small>(eccebombo)</small></a> le <span class="review-date">août 24, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class="review-body">I tested this plugin and found out it didn\'t fit my needs.\nSo I deactivated it and deleted it.\nDoing so made all categories from all post types (custom and classic) being erased from the DataBase.\nI just tested the plugin on one custom post type, and didn\'t activate it anywhere else.\nOne thing I can think of is that I was also using the Taxonomy Order plugin, but, as I said, I didn\'t activate the plugin on any taxonomy.\n\nI don\'t want to be harsh with the authors, I\'m sure they\'re doing a great job, but please be careful and consider testing the scenario I tried to describe, because the damage I had on my DataBase was huge.\n\nThank you very much.</div>\n</div>\n<div class="review">\n	<div class="review-head">\n		<div class="reviewer-info">\n			<div class="review-title-section">\n				<h4 class="review-title">Simple but complete, works perfect!</h4>\n				<div class="star-rating">\n				<div class="wporg-ratings" aria-label="5 sur 5 étoiles" data-title-template="%s sur 5 étoiles" data-rating="5" style="color:#ffb900;"><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class="reviewer">\n				Par <a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/thomaswp"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c71b2e093befe3f06a6681e473dfcb85?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c71b2e093befe3f06a6681e473dfcb85?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' clas